I don't know what you're doing.

244
00:13:52.623 --> 00:13:54.601
If you want answers. you
got to ask me questions.

245
00:13:54.625 --> 00:13:56.645
Okay. here's a question.
Where's roxy now?

246
00:13:56.669 --> 00:13:59.314
Try the dressing room
downstairs. in the basement.

247
00:13:59.338 --> 00:14:00.978
Hey. you go talk to roxy. I'll find Javi.

248
00:14:02.759 --> 00:14:06.739
Once again. thank you. bonbon. for
breaking the case wide open for us.

249
00:14:06.763 --> 00:14:08.032
Here's the key to Atlanta.

250
00:14:08.056 --> 00:14:09.265
Here's a medal of honor.

251
00:14:10.016 --> 00:14:11.785
And tickets to cowboy Carter.

252
00:14:29.952 --> 00:14:31.889
Roxy vásquez?

253
00:14:31.913 --> 00:14:33.998
One moment. I'm not finished yet.

254
00:14:42.715 --> 00:14:44.092
Can I help you?

255
00:14:47.845 --> 00:14:49.222
I'm special agent will Trent.

256
00:14:50.473 --> 00:14:54.745
Right. the man from nowhere.

257
00:14:54.769 --> 00:14:56.270
Do you dance?

258
00:14:57.105 --> 00:14:58.999
No.

259
00:14:59.023 --> 00:15:01.960
I once found a salsa class
on YouTube. It did not go well.

260
00:15:01.984 --> 00:15:04.546
Come on. I'll show you.

261
00:15:06.823 --> 00:15:08.950
I'm not answering
questions unless you do.

262
00:15:10.076 --> 00:15:12.662
Why not?

263
00:15:14.247 --> 00:15:18.227
Okay. So you're gonna start
with your left foot forward.

264
00:15:18.251 --> 00:15:19.436
then you raise your right...

265
00:15:19.460 --> 00:15:21.921
whoa. whoa. Can you…
can you just show me?

266
00:15:23.631 --> 00:15:25.758
Sure. Left.

267
00:15:31.264 --> 00:15:35.017
We've been interviewing people
for hours. You been hiding from us?

268
00:15:35.977 --> 00:15:41.566
I'm not hiding. I needed to
practice. You're off rhythm.

269
00:15:42.316 --> 00:15:44.044
Stop it.

270
00:15:44.068 --> 00:15:45.403
Okay. Don't yell at me.

271
00:15:45.987 --> 00:15:49.365
If I yell at you. you'll know. Look at me.

272
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:54.287
And why are you practicing?

273
00:15:55.121 --> 00:15:56.289
You're not competing.

274
00:15:56.998 --> 00:15:58.934
Catalina Cortez stole your partner.

275
00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:01.711
Although. he is available now. isn't he?

276
00:16:02.712 --> 00:16:04.148
I guess he is.

277
00:16:04.172 --> 00:16:05.339
If you hurry…

278
00:16:06.841 --> 00:16:10.696
You might be able to
scoop him up. agent Trent.

279
00:16:10.720 --> 00:16:11.846
Is it a made-up name?

280
00:16:12.805 --> 00:16:15.016
I'm an orphan. It was given to me.

281
00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:19.812
How did you get those
nasty bruises on your leg?

282
00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:23.375
Comes with dancing.

283
00:16:23.399 --> 00:16:25.401
Catch a heel. take a knee.

284
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:28.738
Part of the job.

285
00:16:30.114 --> 00:16:32.634
Tell me about your
relationship with Catalina Cortez.

286
00:16:32.658 --> 00:16:35.453
Catalina was a pendeja.

287
00:16:36.621 --> 00:16:37.955
She was a bitch.

288
00:16:38.539 --> 00:16:42.019
Thought she deserved the best of
everything. whatever she wanted.

289
00:16:42.043 --> 00:16:44.587
Like she took Javi?

290
00:16:45.838 --> 00:16:47.215
That must've pissed you off?

291
00:16:50.051 --> 00:16:51.219
I'll be fine without Javi.

292
00:16:51.761 --> 00:16:54.055
And I don't wanna make
a whole thing of this. but…

293
00:16:55.389 --> 00:16:57.391
Why didn't you cover up those bruises?

294
00:16:58.226 --> 00:17:01.747
Everyone else is slathered
in body makeup. but not you.

295
00:17:01.771 --> 00:17:04.791
You're paying awfully
close attention to me.

296
00:17:04.815 --> 00:17:05.942
You can count on it.

297
00:17:06.776 --> 00:17:08.361
I'm sorry to interrupt. …

298
00:17:10.571 --> 00:17:12.966
Agent Trent. your
partner's looking for you.

299
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.325
She's down the hall.

300
00:17:21.165 --> 00:17:23.209
To be continued.

301
00:17:25.378 --> 00:17:26.379
Thank you.

302
00:17:31.884 --> 00:17:34.696
He confessed. This was in his backpack.

303
00:17:35.972 --> 00:17:39.100
- Javi.
- I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

304
00:17:40.184 --> 00:17:41.561
You killed Catalina?

305
00:17:42.687 --> 00:17:44.313
Yes. I killed her.

306
00:17:47.858 --> 00:17:50.754
Okay. Javi. we got the labs
back. and this is a match

307
00:17:50.778 --> 00:17:52.798
for the poison used to kill Catalina.

308
00:17:52.822 --> 00:17:54.156
Walk me through how you did it.

309
00:17:54.782 --> 00:17:56.969
I put the poison into her
body makeup and I stirred it in.

310
00:17:56.993 --> 00:17:58.053
and that's what killed her.

311
00:17:58.077 --> 00:17:59.161
How much did you put in?

312
00:18:00.496 --> 00:18:03.475
I don't know. A couple of
shakes. like sugar in your coffee.

313
00:18:03.499 --> 00:18:05.042
- Like sugar in your coffee?
- Yeah.

314
00:18:06.085 --> 00:18:07.086
When did you do this?

315
00:18:07.670 --> 00:18:11.882
Lunchtime? Like noon.

316
00:18:12.925 --> 00:18:15.428
Meaning more than ten
hours before she died?

317
00:18:16.554 --> 00:18:17.638
Yeah.

318
00:18:18.764 --> 00:18:19.849
Okay.

319
00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:24.061
He didn't do it.

320
00:18:25.062 --> 00:18:26.456
How do you know?

321
00:18:26.480 --> 00:18:28.208
Poison breaks down after four hours.

322
00:18:28.232 --> 00:18:30.460
She didn't start getting ready
till seven o'clock that night.

323
00:18:30.484 --> 00:18:31.712
This guy's a patsy.

324
00:18:31.736 --> 00:18:36.073
That's what I'm saying. He's
lying. We're missing something.

325
00:18:38.409 --> 00:18:39.827
Let's get roxy in here.

326
00:18:43.247 --> 00:18:44.707
How long does this usually take?

327
00:18:45.916 --> 00:18:50.022
Depends on the case.
Could be hours. days. weeks.

328
00:18:50.046 --> 00:18:52.232
What?

329
00:18:52.256 --> 00:18:54.359
There's a 20-year-old
baloney sandwich in here.

330
00:18:54.383 --> 00:18:56.111
It's baloney. It's probably still good.

331
00:18:56.135 --> 00:18:57.237
Gross.

332
00:18:57.261 --> 00:18:59.281
Why isn't this all digitized?

333
00:18:59.305 --> 00:19:01.283
Cross-referencing evidence. interviews.

334
00:19:01.307 --> 00:19:03.535
This would take. like. five
minutes instead of five hours.

335
00:19:03.559 --> 00:19:05.203
I'm sorry. is this hard?

336
00:19:05.227 --> 00:19:07.980
Is it hard getting justice
for woodworking Beverly?

337
00:19:08.731 --> 00:19:09.833
It's a cold case.

338
00:19:09.857 --> 00:19:13.378
This is us taking you seriously. It's
what it looks like. Stop complaining.

339
00:19:13.402 --> 00:19:15.714
I don't think expressing an emotion
should be called complaining.

340
00:19:15.738 --> 00:19:17.823
- Shut up.
- Okay. God.

341
00:19:23.496 --> 00:19:25.206
Is this what we're looking for?

342
00:19:29.627 --> 00:19:32.147
Yeah. Yeah. it is.

343
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:34.650
This is the witness statement for
that attack you saw in the paper.

344
00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:38.445
"Sam Lopez saw a yellow
cutlass leaving the scene."

345
00:19:38.469 --> 00:19:42.658
Hey. here's something that
wasn't in the paper. Partial plate.

346
00:19:44.850 --> 00:19:45.851
Yeah.

347
00:19:47.228 --> 00:19:49.873
Okay. here we go.

348
00:19:49.897 --> 00:19:53.043
Registrations on every
yellow oldsmobile cutlass

349
00:19:53.067 --> 00:19:56.362
in Georgia in the year 2003.

350
00:20:01.242 --> 00:20:03.602
Kaia keeps sending me voice
memos. Why do you guys do that?

351
00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:06.431
- Faster.
- Yeah. faster for you. annoying for me.

352
00:20:06.455 --> 00:20:09.017
It's like listening to a
podcast I never subscribed to.

353
00:20:09.041 --> 00:20:11.603
So what do we do now? Like.
how do we narrow this list down?

354
00:20:11.627 --> 00:20:14.272
We cross-reference the names.
see if anyone has a record.

355
00:20:14.296 --> 00:20:18.235
Gonna be a tough road though 'cause
half these people are probably dead by now.

356
00:20:18.259 --> 00:20:19.986
and the other half
definitely don't remember

357
00:20:20.010 --> 00:20:21.571
where they were at
the time of the murder.

358
00:20:21.595 --> 00:20:23.782
That's why I love a fresh
body. The warmer the better.

359
00:20:23.806 --> 00:20:25.951
What are you doing?

360
00:20:25.975 --> 00:20:28.036
Why do you hold it like that?
That's not how you use a phone.

361
00:20:28.060 --> 00:20:29.830
- Hold it normal.
- What is normal?

362
00:20:29.854 --> 00:20:30.914
On speaker.

363
00:20:30.938 --> 00:20:33.375
Speaker? You're the reason
going out in public sucks now.

364
00:20:33.399 --> 00:20:34.751
If you'd listen to your voice memos.

365
00:20:34.775 --> 00:20:37.462
you'd know that Kaia and
detective Polaski got a partial plate.

366
00:20:37.486 --> 00:20:38.487
Starts with the I-f-2.

367
00:20:39.321 --> 00:20:40.882
Ho-ho.

368
00:20:40.906 --> 00:20:42.509
The ladies got a break.

369
00:20:42.533 --> 00:20:47.973
L-f-2 belongs to Wayne hensley.

370
00:20:47.997 --> 00:20:53.520
Mr. Wayne hensley has
multiple misdemeanors.

371
00:20:53.544 --> 00:20:57.399
domestic violence complaints.
no charges ever filed.

372
00:20:57.423 --> 00:20:59.484
Still lives in Atlanta. still alive.

373
00:20:59.508 --> 00:21:01.570
Okay. Yeah. I can dig through his socials.

374
00:21:01.594 --> 00:21:02.779
Maybe he's on TikTok.

375
00:21:02.803 --> 00:21:04.030
He's 65.

376
00:21:04.054 --> 00:21:05.282
Don't be ageist.

377
00:21:05.306 --> 00:21:08.142
I have a better idea. Stakeout.

378
00:21:08.726 --> 00:21:09.894
Really?

379
00:21:10.978 --> 00:21:11.979
Let's go. meat.

380
00:21:16.942 --> 00:21:18.336
Do you recognize this?

381
00:21:20.821 --> 00:21:22.531
Yeah. that's my body makeup.

382
00:21:23.491 --> 00:21:25.260
I thought so.

383
00:21:25.284 --> 00:21:28.454
'Cause it's the same body
makeup used to poison Catalina.

384
00:21:29.830 --> 00:21:32.583
- What?
- Javi is lying.

385
00:21:33.167 --> 00:21:34.835
He's covering for someone.

386
00:21:35.878 --> 00:21:37.022
I think it's you.

387
00:21:37.046 --> 00:21:39.357
Catalina stole your dance partner. right?

388
00:21:39.381 --> 00:21:41.818
And in doing so. she
stole 100 grand from you.

389
00:21:41.842 --> 00:21:44.196
- I-I didn't kill her.
- Then how did she get your makeup?

390
00:21:44.220 --> 00:21:45.221
I don't know.

391
00:21:45.971 --> 00:21:47.264
She probably stole it.

392
00:21:47.807 --> 00:21:51.369
Like she swiped my dress last
year and then lied to my face about it.

393
00:21:51.393 --> 00:21:52.913
She thinks the world belongs to her.

394
00:21:52.937 --> 00:21:55.189
Ask anyone. She just takes things.

395
00:22:00.778 --> 00:22:06.575
If Catalina stole your makeup. it
means she wasn't the target. you were.

396
00:22:08.160 --> 00:22:09.995
Why would someone want you dead?

397
00:22:11.247 --> 00:22:15.209
If you know something.
now's the time to talk.

398
00:22:18.212 --> 00:22:20.923
Roxy. I don't know what's going on.

399
00:22:21.674 --> 00:22:25.302
But if you're in trouble. I can help you.

400
00:22:28.806 --> 00:22:29.849
How?

401
00:22:31.517 --> 00:22:33.602
How you can help me?

402
00:22:34.353 --> 00:22:35.747
You don't know me.

403
00:22:35.771 --> 00:22:37.040
You don't know this world.

404
00:22:37.064 --> 00:22:38.524
You don't know these people.

405
00:22:40.901 --> 00:22:41.986
I'm done talking.

406
00:22:57.293 --> 00:22:59.688
We're just gonna follow
this guy around all day?

407
00:22:59.712 --> 00:23:01.088
I have other classes. you know.

408
00:23:02.089 --> 00:23:04.943
Yeah. I was on a stakeout
for three days once.

409
00:23:04.967 --> 00:23:09.823
No shower. no bed. just
me. 400 bags of funyuns.

410
00:23:09.847 --> 00:23:11.283
Wish this was a funyun.

411
00:23:11.307 --> 00:23:13.058
Can't you just arrest
him and run his DNA?

412
00:23:14.101 --> 00:23:16.037
For what? Man's doing his laundry.

413
00:23:16.061 --> 00:23:19.374
We have to wait and hope
that he leaves some DNA behind

414
00:23:19.398 --> 00:23:22.252
someplace where there's no
reasonable expectation of privacy.

415
00:23:22.276 --> 00:23:23.986
Like maybe on that
cigarette he's smoking.

416
00:23:35.205 --> 00:23:36.999
Come on.

417
00:23:38.000 --> 00:23:39.084
Who does that?

418
00:23:41.962 --> 00:23:43.881
Hey. All right.

419
00:23:45.799 --> 00:23:49.070
- What'd I miss?
- He doesn't use fabric softener.

420
00:23:49.094 --> 00:23:51.865
Fabric softeners are a scam. Your
clothes are already soft enough.

421
00:23:51.889 --> 00:23:53.349
Hey. look at this.

422
00:24:03.734 --> 00:24:05.128
Here we go.

423
00:24:05.152 --> 00:24:07.029
Just leave it. man.
Walk away. walk away.

424
00:24:12.451 --> 00:24:14.763
- This guy's killing me.
- Damn it. Wayne. what are you doing?

425
00:24:14.787 --> 00:24:16.997
Making an art installation
with your DNA trash?

426
00:24:17.581 --> 00:24:18.975
I have to get out of this car.

427
00:24:18.999 --> 00:24:21.251
Kaia. Take a walk.

428
00:24:33.847 --> 00:24:36.809
Right in the ear. really? Right in my ear.

429
00:24:40.020 --> 00:24:42.791
I'm gonna have this baby in this car.

430
00:24:42.815 --> 00:24:44.000
My stomach hurts.

431
00:24:44.024 --> 00:24:47.420
If anyone farts. I swear to god.
there will be another murder.

432
00:24:47.444 --> 00:24:49.697
And there's not a jury in
the world who will convict me.

433
00:24:56.495 --> 00:24:59.015
God. He's leaving.
This whole thing's a bust.

434
00:24:59.039 --> 00:25:00.266
Okay. forget it. I give up.

435
00:25:00.290 --> 00:25:02.018
I don't care who
murdered Beverly Rutledge.

436
00:25:02.042 --> 00:25:04.169
I don't care about justice.
I just wanna go home.

437
00:25:04.712 --> 00:25:06.463
Kaia. it's been 90 minutes.

438
00:25:12.344 --> 00:25:13.345
Gum!

439
00:25:14.013 --> 00:25:18.976
Hallelujah. Let's get this
murder gum and go the hell home.

440
00:25:24.398 --> 00:25:27.526
When I found out my
mother was from Puerto Rico.

441
00:25:29.111 --> 00:25:33.991
for the first time in my life. I
knew something about myself.

442
00:25:35.909 --> 00:25:40.098
And I thought that meant I
got to be a part of something.

443
00:25:40.122 --> 00:25:43.250
Suddenly. I had this history.

444
00:25:43.917 --> 00:25:47.171
I came from a people. a lineage.

445
00:25:49.214 --> 00:25:50.632
Felt like I had an anchor.

446
00:25:53.343 --> 00:25:55.345
Like I finally found a piece of…

447
00:25:58.432 --> 00:25:59.641
Home.

448
00:26:00.851 --> 00:26:03.580
But to these people… …I'm nothing.

449
00:26:03.604 --> 00:26:05.898
I'm less than nothing. I'm an outsider.

450
00:26:06.565 --> 00:26:08.251
My Spanish is terrible.

451
00:26:08.275 --> 00:26:09.485
I don't dance salsa.

452
00:26:10.152 --> 00:26:13.173
Everything I learned about
my heritage came from a book.

453
00:26:13.197 --> 00:26:15.449
Not even a book. an audiobook.

454
00:26:18.243 --> 00:26:20.597
Whatever. Who cares?
Look. are we done?

455
00:26:20.621 --> 00:26:23.141
I don't have time for this.
I'm in the middle of a case.

456
00:26:23.165 --> 00:26:26.102
Don't do that. Everything
you're saying matters.

457
00:26:26.126 --> 00:26:28.462
And by the way. we are
talking about the case.

458
00:26:34.968 --> 00:26:40.766
You know. when I was a kid
and things were really bad…

459
00:26:42.101 --> 00:26:44.204
I used to try to disappear.

460
00:26:45.354 --> 00:26:48.458
Don't call attention. don't make noise.

461
00:26:48.482 --> 00:26:50.442
And if I tried hard…

462
00:26:54.863 --> 00:26:56.990
It was like I was there but…

463
00:26:59.118 --> 00:27:01.328
…I really wasn't.

464
00:27:02.454 --> 00:27:03.455
That's how this feels.

465
00:27:04.123 --> 00:27:07.060
I'm the man from nowhere.

466
00:27:07.084 --> 00:27:09.086
It's pathetic. I know.

467
00:27:09.878 --> 00:27:14.484
When I was in college. I went to Korea
with three other Koreans from Georgia.

468
00:27:14.508 --> 00:27:19.763
Everybody in Seoul saw right
through us. big dumb Georgia Koreans.

469
00:27:20.597 --> 00:27:22.826
But that didn't mean we weren't Korean.

470
00:27:22.850 --> 00:27:26.830
Just because you feel a
barrier to entry into your culture

471
00:27:26.854 --> 00:27:28.790
doesn't mean it's not yours.

472
00:27:28.814 --> 00:27:31.042
It's absolutely yours.

473
00:27:31.066 --> 00:27:33.127
I feel so outside.

474
00:27:33.151 --> 00:27:37.030
So. what can we do to center
you? What can you fall back on?

475
00:27:37.781 --> 00:27:40.635
Solving Catalina Cortez's murder.

476
00:27:40.659 --> 00:27:43.161
Good. I like that.

477
00:27:43.829 --> 00:27:46.558
Do your job. stand up for her.

478
00:27:46.582 --> 00:27:49.352
These people don't know you. but I do.

479
00:27:49.376 --> 00:27:52.212
This killer is underestimating you. Good.

480
00:27:53.088 --> 00:27:54.965
They won't even see you coming.

481
00:28:00.971 --> 00:28:03.015
Take a swig. You're still
building your tolerance.

482
00:28:07.185 --> 00:28:08.265
I think it was the funyuns.

483
00:28:08.979 --> 00:28:11.958
- Pete. please tell me you got good news.
- Looks like you got a bad guy.

484
00:28:11.982 --> 00:28:13.042
- Yeah.
- Sweet.

485
00:28:13.066 --> 00:28:14.586
Lab ran the DNA from the gum.

486
00:28:14.610 --> 00:28:18.423
It's a full match on three
separate rape kits. It's conclusive.

487
00:28:18.447 --> 00:28:20.884
I briefed special victims.
They're picking him up now.

488
00:28:20.908 --> 00:28:22.927
- What about Beverly Rutledge?
- Not a match.

489
00:28:22.951 --> 00:28:24.637
Whoever killed her. it wasn't him.

490
00:28:24.661 --> 00:28:26.079
- Thanks. Pete.
- Yep.

491
00:28:27.372 --> 00:28:32.645
Hey. look. you just solved
three sexual assault cases.

492
00:28:32.669 --> 00:28:33.730
This is huge.

493
00:28:33.754 --> 00:28:37.841
No. yeah. I know. good. I just
thought we solved a murder.

494
00:28:38.800 --> 00:28:41.428
Wait. so what now?
The case just dies again?

495
00:28:42.054 --> 00:28:44.991
No. I wanna talk to Toni.

496
00:28:45.015 --> 00:28:48.411
They wrote her off because
she was unreliable. unstable.

497
00:28:48.435 --> 00:28:50.187
My kind of gal. Let's bring her in.

498
00:28:51.146 --> 00:28:54.292
Javi's lying to us. and roxy's
not telling us what she knows.

499
00:28:54.316 --> 00:28:57.086
So. you've come to
encyclopedia bonbon.

500
00:28:57.110 --> 00:28:59.547
Let's start with what you
know about Javi amenos.

501
00:28:59.571 --> 00:29:03.593
Javi's drowning. Money problems.

502
00:29:03.617 --> 00:29:06.220
His family's in trouble
trying to get out of Colombia.

503
00:29:06.244 --> 00:29:08.139
He's scraping cash any way he can.

504
00:29:08.163 --> 00:29:11.124
Sounds like motive to lie. He's
being paid to be the fall guy.

505
00:29:12.334 --> 00:29:13.728
What do you know about roxy vásquez?

506
00:29:13.752 --> 00:29:15.521
Roxy. roxy. roxy.

507
00:29:15.545 --> 00:29:17.941
- She loves oysters.
- Okay.

508
00:29:17.965 --> 00:29:22.028
She got a dog named chu.
Pikachu. Not choo choo. like the train.

509
00:29:22.052 --> 00:29:25.222
Anything that could tell us
who wanted roxy dead. bonbon.

510
00:29:26.056 --> 00:29:29.327
I'm accessing the memory
palace. You know. it takes a minute.

511
00:29:29.351 --> 00:29:31.204
- Whenever you're ready.
- Thank you.

512
00:29:31.228 --> 00:29:35.208
Okay. here's something I have
noticed. but you tell me if it's relevant.

513
00:29:35.232 --> 00:29:36.626
Y'all the detectives.

514
00:29:36.650 --> 00:29:41.029
Every time ramos delgado
checks-in to a hotel on business.

515
00:29:41.613 --> 00:29:44.050
the socials put roxy within blocks of him.

516
00:29:44.074 --> 00:29:46.135
You think roxy's having
an affair with ramos?

517
00:29:46.159 --> 00:29:49.472
Well. you said it. not me. I'm
just a lonely observer of facts.

518
00:29:49.496 --> 00:29:53.142
If that is true. we need to be
looking at his wife. Isabella.

519
00:29:53.166 --> 00:29:55.186
Kill the woman who's
sleeping with her husband.

520
00:29:55.210 --> 00:29:56.896
Keep his money and his status.

521
00:29:56.920 --> 00:29:59.315
If you want to talk. you
better talk to them fast.

522
00:29:59.339 --> 00:30:01.526
because they're going to
Colombia after the finals.

523
00:30:01.550 --> 00:30:04.153
Ramos is the guest of honor at
some luncheon for rich people.

524
00:30:04.177 --> 00:30:05.863
Which. like. what even
is a luncheon anyways?

525
00:30:05.887 --> 00:30:07.156
Like. just say lunch.

526
00:30:07.180 --> 00:30:09.867
We can't hold Isabella.
She has diplomatic immunity.

527
00:30:09.891 --> 00:30:13.246
We need hard evidence to petition
the Colombian government to revoke it.

528
00:30:13.270 --> 00:30:15.123
We only have 24 hours.

529
00:30:15.147 --> 00:30:16.833
Let's loop in Amanda.

530
00:30:16.857 --> 00:30:19.293
Have her bring them in. Say
that she has an update for them.

531
00:30:19.317 --> 00:30:21.671
Maybe we can rattle his cage
and see what shakes loose.

532
00:30:26.116 --> 00:30:27.242
Can I go?

533
00:30:33.749 --> 00:30:36.144
Y'all didn't want to hear me 20 years ago.

534
00:30:36.168 --> 00:30:38.104
Why should I say anything now?

535
00:30:38.128 --> 00:30:42.049
Well. we don't always get
it right. We're trying to now.

536
00:30:43.133 --> 00:30:44.777
You said in your original statement.

537
00:30:44.801 --> 00:30:47.739
Beverly was the only one who
cared what was happening to you.

538
00:30:47.763 --> 00:30:49.240
What'd you mean by that?

539
00:30:49.264 --> 00:30:50.599
She was kind.

540
00:30:51.892 --> 00:30:54.102
Not a lot of people are
nice to convicts. you know.

541
00:30:54.728 --> 00:30:56.980
They don't… they don't
think we can change.

542
00:30:57.689 --> 00:31:00.626
But not bev. She let
me hang out in her shop.

543
00:31:00.650 --> 00:31:02.986
- Woodworking. right?
- Yeah.

544
00:31:04.029 --> 00:31:07.240
That place always smelled
like sawdust and pine.

545
00:31:07.866 --> 00:31:09.743
She told me I can come
by whenever I wanted.

546
00:31:10.368 --> 00:31:11.804
She help you make that?

547
00:31:11.828 --> 00:31:15.207
Yeah. It's a habit by now.

548
00:31:15.957 --> 00:31:17.375
May I?

549
00:31:22.839 --> 00:31:24.150
It's beautiful.

550
00:31:24.174 --> 00:31:25.592
It's the first thing I ever made.

551
00:31:26.384 --> 00:31:28.428
Got me through a lot in that house.

552
00:31:29.137 --> 00:31:32.325
The halfway house?
What was going on there?

553
00:31:38.814 --> 00:31:42.234
If you wanna talk. I'll listen.

554
00:31:43.735 --> 00:31:44.945
Started with favors.

555
00:31:45.737 --> 00:31:48.549
You know. you'd break
a rule. and Jim would...

556
00:31:48.573 --> 00:31:49.884
who's Jim?

557
00:31:49.908 --> 00:31:51.827
Jim Branson.

558
00:31:52.494 --> 00:31:53.578
The house manager.

559
00:31:55.372 --> 00:31:57.600
He looked the other
way if you did him a favor.

560
00:31:57.624 --> 00:31:59.227
We're talking sexual favors?

561
00:31:59.251 --> 00:32:02.337
Come on. Lady. you know.

562
00:32:04.005 --> 00:32:06.651
Yeah. I do.

563
00:32:06.675 --> 00:32:09.052
But all those favors turned
into a deal with the devil.

564
00:32:10.887 --> 00:32:14.558
With a record. it's near impossible
to find a place to live. and he knew it.

565
00:32:15.100 --> 00:32:16.268
You couldn't pay rent.

566
00:32:17.060 --> 00:32:21.022
Yeah. Jim would make
sure you earn it his way.

567
00:32:22.315 --> 00:32:24.151
He brought guys in and charged them.

568
00:32:26.111 --> 00:32:30.031
I'm so sorry. Toni. Did
Beverly know about it?

569
00:32:30.615 --> 00:32:31.884
I told her.

570
00:32:31.908 --> 00:32:34.053
And she said she's gonna talk to Jim.

571
00:32:34.077 --> 00:32:37.581
Call the cops if she
needed to. Put an end to it.

572
00:32:39.374 --> 00:32:40.667
Week later. she was killed.

573
00:32:45.881 --> 00:32:48.925
We will do everything in
our power to put this right.

574
00:32:51.052 --> 00:32:52.762
This case isn't what I expected.

575
00:32:54.222 --> 00:32:55.223
They never are.

576
00:33:01.146 --> 00:33:03.374
Deputy director. thank
you for taking the time

577
00:33:03.398 --> 00:33:06.210
- to meet with us before we fly tonight.
- Of course.

578
00:33:06.234 --> 00:33:08.212
Happy to give you an update.

579
00:33:08.236 --> 00:33:09.589
Please come in.

580
00:33:09.613 --> 00:33:11.156
- My god.
- What?

581
00:33:13.867 --> 00:33:16.721
So. you have an update for us.

582
00:33:16.745 --> 00:33:19.098
Sorry for the. interruption.

583
00:33:19.122 --> 00:33:22.250
Catalina's belongings
still need to be released.

584
00:33:23.043 --> 00:33:26.772
Mr. Delgado. if you wouldn't mind
going with me to property for a signature.

585
00:33:26.796 --> 00:33:29.233
That's right. I completely forgot.

586
00:33:29.257 --> 00:33:30.693
Thanks for the reminder.

587
00:33:30.717 --> 00:33:33.094
It's right this way. It won't take long.

588
00:33:33.887 --> 00:33:34.888
Of course.

589
00:33:37.766 --> 00:33:38.975
Isabella.

590
00:33:40.518 --> 00:33:41.728
We don't have much time.

591
00:33:42.312 --> 00:33:45.273
I saw your tattoo. the flor de maga.

592
00:33:45.941 --> 00:33:49.212
Roxy has one too. Only
hers is a hummingbird.

593
00:33:49.236 --> 00:33:50.755
You know the story. don't you?

594
00:33:53.531 --> 00:33:56.618
Two lovers torn apart.
couldn't be together.

595
00:34:01.498 --> 00:34:04.793
The gods took pity on them and
turned one of them into a hummingbird.

596
00:34:07.462 --> 00:34:09.339
And the other one into a flower…

597
00:34:12.425 --> 00:34:14.719
So they could always find
their way back to each other.

598
00:34:25.939 --> 00:34:28.733
You and roxy are having an affair.

599
00:34:29.609 --> 00:34:33.238
Your husband found out. He
tried to kill her because of it.

600
00:34:34.281 --> 00:34:35.591
Is that true. Ms. Delgado?

601
00:34:35.615 --> 00:34:38.076
Don't. Don't. please.

602
00:34:39.869 --> 00:34:45.726
We leave right after the final dance.
There's nothing you can do about it.

603
00:34:45.750 --> 00:34:49.921
- We can protect you.
- No. no. You… you can't.

604
00:34:52.048 --> 00:34:53.216
You don't know him.

605
00:34:55.552 --> 00:34:56.553
Please?

606
00:34:58.221 --> 00:34:59.306
Leave it alone.

607
00:35:00.307 --> 00:35:01.308
Yeah?

608
00:35:03.643 --> 00:35:04.644
Yeah.

609
00:35:10.400 --> 00:35:12.235
Tell ramos I'll be in the car.

610
00:35:18.950 --> 00:35:20.243
What now?

611
00:35:22.787 --> 00:35:23.788
We get him.

612
00:35:24.873 --> 00:35:25.933
Yeah. perfect. Thank you.

613
00:35:25.957 --> 00:35:27.059
Guys. we got it.

614
00:35:27.083 --> 00:35:29.562
Judge just signed off on
the warrant for Jim Branson.

615
00:35:29.586 --> 00:35:32.481
- Where's Kaia? We gotta go.
- Caffeine run. Thought we'd be here late.

616
00:35:32.505 --> 00:35:33.983
You're learning.

617
00:35:34.007 --> 00:35:36.485
Though she did take
my order a while ago. so…

618
00:35:36.509 --> 00:35:39.572
These damn voice memos.
Three in the last hour.

619
00:35:39.596 --> 00:35:41.076
Are you ever going to listen to them?

620
00:35:42.015 --> 00:35:45.375
Fine. Okay? But I'm gonna do it on speaker
and I don't wanna hear anything about it.

621
00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:48.414
Hey. detective. I know you
said you wanted drip coffee.

622
00:35:48.438 --> 00:35:50.082
but have you ever had match a?

623
00:35:50.106 --> 00:35:51.709
I think you'd really like it.

624
00:35:51.733 --> 00:35:53.336
Let me know if you wanna switch it up.

625
00:35:53.360 --> 00:35:55.129
No. match a tastes like lawn.

626
00:35:55.153 --> 00:35:57.757
Line's brutal.

627
00:35:57.781 --> 00:36:00.509
There's still time to change your
mind if you want to try the match a.

628
00:36:00.533 --> 00:36:03.846
It's great with oat milk. You
know what? I'll just get you both.

629
00:36:03.870 --> 00:36:05.931
No. Why would she do that?

630
00:36:05.955 --> 00:36:08.434
- I'll drink it.
- How many more of these are there?

631
00:36:08.458 --> 00:36:10.478
Just one. thank god.

632
00:36:10.502 --> 00:36:13.981
Okay. wrapping up at the coffee
shop. You know what's cray?

633
00:36:14.005 --> 00:36:16.692
Jim Branson's current address
is just a few minutes away.

634
00:36:16.716 --> 00:36:17.777
I'm gonna swing by.

635
00:36:17.801 --> 00:36:20.279
If it's trash night. maybe I can
snag DNA like you showed us.

636
00:36:20.303 --> 00:36:22.681
- I'll keep you posted.
- Damn it. Kaia.

637
00:36:35.652 --> 00:36:37.372
What the hell are you
doing on my property?

638
00:36:39.030 --> 00:36:42.951
I'm making a citizen's arrest for
the murder of Beverly Rutledge.

639
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:45.662
What did you just say to me?

640
00:36:46.329 --> 00:36:49.934
I meant to say. this is a citizen's arrest.

641
00:37:04.681 --> 00:37:09.036
Jim Branson. you're under arrest
for solicitation. human trafficking…

642
00:37:09.060 --> 00:37:10.663
Hey. stay. You stay here.

643
00:37:10.687 --> 00:37:12.373
You have the right to remain silent.

644
00:37:12.397 --> 00:37:15.126
Anything you say can and will be
used against you in a court of law.

645
00:37:15.150 --> 00:37:17.962
- Hey. you all right?
- Yeah.

646
00:37:17.986 --> 00:37:20.363
- You sure?
- Yeah.

647
00:37:20.864 --> 00:37:22.425
Dude. that was so dumb.

648
00:37:22.449 --> 00:37:23.616
Let's go.

649
00:37:25.410 --> 00:37:28.097
Okay. An intern no
more. Let's get you home.

650
00:37:41.468 --> 00:37:42.611
It's Javi and roxy.

651
00:38:02.489 --> 00:38:05.342
Why is that man not in
custody? He's a murderer.

652
00:38:05.366 --> 00:38:07.803
I'm not prosecuting a man
we both know didn't do it.

653
00:38:07.827 --> 00:38:10.264
What the hell are you talking
about? I-I heard he confessed.

654
00:38:10.288 --> 00:38:12.081
You know. I have a different theory.

655
00:38:12.957 --> 00:38:15.895
Catalina. she was collateral damage.

656
00:38:15.919 --> 00:38:19.190
You wanted roxy gone because
Isabella was gonna leave you for her.

657
00:38:19.214 --> 00:38:22.234
And that just ate at you.
And so you did something.

658
00:38:22.258 --> 00:38:24.236
That's a big accusation to make. agent.

659
00:38:24.260 --> 00:38:26.137
Yeah. well. there's precedent. isn't there?

660
00:38:26.721 --> 00:38:30.242
Six years ago. senator Ernesto
castaño. your biggest rival.

661
00:38:30.266 --> 00:38:32.703
drops dead at a political rally?

662
00:38:32.727 --> 00:38:35.122
Yeah. we obtained his autopsy report.

663
00:38:36.314 --> 00:38:39.776
Aconitine. Same poison
used to kill Catalina.

664
00:38:42.403 --> 00:38:45.216
If you did your homework. you
also learned I was never charged.

665
00:38:45.240 --> 00:38:47.843
Yeah. because you
handpicked the prosecutor.

666
00:38:47.867 --> 00:38:51.430
Even if that were true. and
it's not. you'll never touch me.

667
00:38:51.454 --> 00:38:53.516
Diplomatic immunity protects me.

668
00:38:53.540 --> 00:38:56.751
That eats at you. doesn't it. hermano?

669
00:38:57.418 --> 00:38:58.646
I'm not your hermano.

670
00:38:58.670 --> 00:39:00.898
You're not.

671
00:39:00.922 --> 00:39:02.733
I did my research too.

672
00:39:02.757 --> 00:39:06.904
It must gnaw at you. coming from
nothing. always being on the outside.

673
00:39:06.928 --> 00:39:09.681
Same way it kills you
knowing you can't put me away.

674
00:39:10.390 --> 00:39:11.391
And you know that.

675
00:39:13.685 --> 00:39:15.621
Catalina didn't do
anything to deserve this.

676
00:39:15.645 --> 00:39:18.982
No. she didn't. It's just
the cost of doing business.

677
00:39:20.400 --> 00:39:22.277
No one crosses me.

678
00:39:23.486 --> 00:39:25.798
Nothing that's mine will
ever be taken from me.

679
00:39:25.822 --> 00:39:28.950
Not my seat. Not my
money. Not my wife.

680
00:39:38.042 --> 00:39:39.085
You get all that. faith?

681
00:39:40.962 --> 00:39:43.381
Yes. we did.

682
00:39:45.008 --> 00:39:47.736
We spoke to the Colombian
government and the state department.

683
00:39:47.760 --> 00:39:52.015
Your immunity is revoked.
You're gonna be charged here.

684
00:39:57.395 --> 00:39:58.581
I want my attorney.

685
00:39:58.605 --> 00:40:01.065
- Sure. Yeah. you should do that.
- Let's go.

686
00:40:13.786 --> 00:40:16.497
The hummingbird and flor de maga.

687
00:40:18.791 --> 00:40:20.269
And now we can be together

688
00:40:20.293 --> 00:40:23.731
because the man from nowhere
knew the old taino legend

689
00:40:23.755 --> 00:40:24.940
from the island. right?

690
00:40:24.964 --> 00:40:27.008
I must've come across it in a book.

691
00:40:28.134 --> 00:40:30.553
Thank you. agent Trent.

692
00:40:31.054 --> 00:40:35.784
You know. Puerto Rico could
be the place for our new start.

693
00:40:37.810 --> 00:40:39.663
- I'd love that for us.
- Yeah.

694
00:40:39.687 --> 00:40:42.148
I'll look you all up next time I visit.

695
00:40:42.941 --> 00:40:44.835
Please.

696
00:40:44.859 --> 00:40:47.796
You wanna come dance?
You could work on your salsa.

697
00:40:51.407 --> 00:40:53.594
Yeah. I… I really gotta go.

698
00:40:53.618 --> 00:40:56.621
What? You got a girl
waiting at home for you?

699
00:40:58.164 --> 00:40:59.165
Maybe.

700
00:41:03.670 --> 00:41:05.004
- I love you.
- I love you.

701
00:41:09.717 --> 00:41:13.596
No. I don't just have any girl waiting.

702
00:41:14.347 --> 00:41:17.701
I have a gorgeous girl waiting for me.

703
00:41:19.560 --> 00:41:21.622
Isn't that right. Betty?

704
00:41:23.773 --> 00:41:25.400
Let me show you what I learned today.

705
00:41:26.943 --> 00:41:28.778
You ready? Yeah.

706
00:41:29.570 --> 00:41:31.864
That's my girl.

707
00:41:37.286 --> 00:41:38.830
Something like this. I don't know.

708
00:41:50.008 --> 00:41:51.402
That's my girl.

709
00:41:51.426 --> 00:41:52.695
Yeah.

709
